                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-290-off1599 t18290910-290-crimeloc1602"></join> on the 4th of September, the officer asked if I had lost a handkerchief - I felt, and it was gone; he went and fetched the prisoner, and this handkerchief, which I believe is mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290910-290-person2704">
                  JOHN 
                  GIRTON
               <interp inst="t18290910-290-person2704" type="surname" value="GIRTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-290-person2704" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290910-290-person2704" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw this gentleman in Abchurch-lane - I saw the prisoner go up by the Post-office, put his hand into this gentleman's pocket, and take out the handkerchief; I told the gentleman, then went and took the prisoner with it, between his breast and his waistcoat - he took it out and threw it down; there were others with him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did not take it at all.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character, and his father promised to take care of him.</p>
               <p>
